<subSubSection id="3EA46D4198B4E02D87451CD7229ADE56" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="851BA61870B46D90F4F92FFAABE805FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="811624218B6C93DBA732A16DF55D74AF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">This species is distinct because of the erect habit and the persistent ovate bracts, which almost clasp the calyx as the pedicels are very short.</paragraph>
